<subSubSection pageId="87" pageNumber="88" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="87.[151,1437,906,1903]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1626,1651]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ashmead" baseAuthorityYear="1887" box="[670,789,1626,1651]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandis">
<emphasis box="[670,789,1626,1651]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">A. grandis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the head wider than long; the frontal angle of the ocellar triangle acute; the clypeus distinctly wide and long; the transverse pronotal carina followed by foveae and with a very small longitudinal carina; the pronotal disc with a median longitudinal line; and the metapostnotum with all carinae parallel, and with first metapostnotal carina complete, whereas 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ashmead" baseAuthorityYear="1887" box="[1047,1164,1734,1759]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandis">
<emphasis box="[1047,1164,1734,1759]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">A. grandis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the head as wide as long; the frontal angle of the ocellae forming a right angle; the clypeus rounded, short, and with an apical median tooth; the transverse pronotal carina without foveae and with a small longitudinal carina; the pronotal disc without a median longitudinal line; and the metapostnotum with the metapostnotal-propodeal suture convergent to the first pair of metapostnotal carinae.
</paragraph>
